							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/nataliethezutter/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/9EOz6Pc8_400x400-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Natalie Zutter" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/nataliethezutter/">Natalie Zutter</a></h6>
										<strong>Natalie Zutter</strong> is a Brooklyn-based playwright and pop culture critic whose work has appeared on Tor.com, NPR Books, <em>Den of Geek</em>, and elsewhere. Find her on Twitter <a class="external" href="https://twitter.com/nataliezutter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@nataliezutter</a>.																			</div>
